<!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
<!-- Use the Introduction section to give a brief overview of what
     the applet is and what it does. -->
  <sect1 id="modemlights-introduction"> 
	 <title>Introduction</title> 
	 <!-- ==== Figure ============================================= -->
	 <figure id="applet-fig"> 
		<title>&applet; Applet</title> 
		<screenshot> 
		  <mediaobject> 
			 <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet.png"
				format="PNG"/> 
			 </imageobject>
			 <textobject> 
				<phrase>Shows &applet; applet. Contains a dial up button and modem light status indicators,
				</phrase> 
			 </textobject> 
		  </mediaobject> 
		</screenshot> 
	 </figure> 
    	<!-- ==== End of Figure ======================================= -->
	<para>The <application>&applet;</application> applet enables you to make
        a dial up connection to the internet and monitor the modem status. You can customize the modem status
        indicators with different colors for Receive data, Send data, Connection status and Text. You can also
        select the Connect and Disconnect commands.
        </para>
	<para>To add <application>&applet;</application> to a panel, right-click on the panel, then choose <menuchoice>
	<guimenu>Add to Panel</guimenu>
	<guisubmenu>Internet</guisubmenu>
	<guimenuitem>&applet;</guimenuitem>
	</menuchoice>.
	The layout of the <application>&applet;</application> applet varies depending on the size and type
	of panel in which the applet resides.</para>
  </sect1>

<!-- ================ Usage ================================ -->
<!-- Use this section to describe how to use the applet to perform the tasks for 
     which the applet is designed. -->
  <sect1 id="modemlights-usage"> 
    <title>Usage</title> 
      <itemizedlist> 
        <listitem> 
          <para> 
            <xref linkend="modemlights-connect"/>
          </para> 
	</listitem> 
        <listitem> 
	  <para> 
	    <xref linkend="modemlights-disconnect"/>
          </para> 
        </listitem> 
      </itemizedlist> 

      <sect2 id="modemlights-connect">
        <title>To Dial up</title>
	<para>To make a dial up connection to the internet, right click on the 
          <inlinemediaobject>
	    <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_button.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
    	    <textobject>
              <phrase>Shows connect/disconnect button.</phrase>
            </textobject>
          </inlinemediaobject> button. 
        </para>
        <para>
        The applet displays the following Confirm connection dialog box, as shown in <xref linkend="fig-if-connect"/>
	<figure id="fig-if-connect"> 
	  <title>Connection Confirmation Dialog Box</title> 
	  <screenshot> 
	    <mediaobject> 
	      <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_if_connect.png" format="PNG"/> 
              </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; connection confirm dialog box.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
	    </mediaobject> 
	  </screenshot> 
	</figure> 
        </para>
        <para>
        Press the <guibutton>Yes</guibutton> button if you want to connect to the internet, 
        press the <guibutton>No</guibutton> button if don't want to connect to the internet.
        </para>
        <para>
        If you select the <guibutton>Yes</guibutton> button to connect to the internet, the &applet; applet 
        will display the awaiting connection status, as shown in <xref linkend="fig-awaiting-connect"/>
 	<figure id="fig-awaiting-connect"> 
	  <title>&applet; Applet Status While Awaiting Connection</title> 
	  <screenshot> 
	    <mediaobject> 
	      <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_awaiting.png" format="PNG"/> 
	      </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; shows awaiting connection status.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
	    </mediaobject> 
	  </screenshot> 
	</figure>        
        </para>
        <para>
        Once the connection is established, the &applet; applet will display the Connected status, as 
        shown in <xref linkend="fig-connecting"/> 
 	<figure id="fig-connecting"> 
	<title>&applet; Applet Status While Connected</title> 
	  <screenshot> 
	    <mediaobject> 
	      <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_connected.png" format="PNG"/> 
			 </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
              <phrase>Shows &applet; shows modem receive data, send data and connection status. </phrase> 
              </textobject> 
	    </mediaobject> 
	  </screenshot> 
	</figure>   
        </para>
      </sect2>

      <sect2 id="modemlights-disconnect">
        <title>To Disconnect</title>
	<para>To disconnect a modem, right click on the 
  	  <inlinemediaobject>
	    <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_button_2.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
    	    <textobject>
              <phrase>Shows connect/disconnect button.</phrase>
            </textobject>
          </inlinemediaobject> button. 
        </para>
        <para>
        Once the modem is disconnected, the &applet; applet will be shown as in <xref linkend="fig-disconnecting"/>
 	<figure id="fig-disconnecting"> 
	<title>&applet; Applet Status While Modem is Disconnected</title> 
	  <screenshot> 
	    <mediaobject> 
	      <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_not_connected.png" format="PNG"/> 
	      </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; shows modem disconnection status.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
	    </mediaobject> 
	  </screenshot> 
	</figure> 
        </para>
      </sect2>
  </sect1>

<!-- ============= Preferences =========================== -->
  <sect1 id="modemlights-prefs">
    <title>Preferences</title>
      <para>To configure <application>&applet;</application>, right-click on the
	    applet, then choose <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem> from the popup menu.
      </para> 
      <para>The <guimenuitem>Properties</guimenuitem> dialog contains the following
            tabbed sections: 
      </para> 
      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem> 
          <para><xref linkend="modemlights-prefs-general"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
         <listitem> 
          <para><xref linkend="modemlights-prefs-color"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem> 
          <para><xref linkend="modemlights-prefs-advanced"/>
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <sect2 id="modemlights-prefs-general">
        <title>General</title>
        <para>The <guilabel>General</guilabel> tab has the following screenshot, as shown in 
              <xref linkend="fig-prefs-general"/>, which you can use to set Display status, commands for Connect
              and Disconnect.</para>
        <figure id="fig-prefs-general">
          <title>General Preferences</title>
          <screenshot>
            <mediaobject>
              <imageobject>
              <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_general.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
              <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; applet general preferences tab.</phrase>
              </textobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </screenshot>
        </figure>
	<variablelist> 
	  <varlistentry> 
            <term> 
	      <guilabel>Connecting</guilabel>
            </term> 
 	    <listitem>
            <para>This section allows you to enter a command to use for Connecting to internet, to Disconnect it.
                  It also allows you to select whether you want a Confirm connection dialog being pop up.
            </para>
            <figure id="fig-prefs-general-connecting"> 
              <title>Connecting Preferences</title> 
              <screenshot> 
              <mediaobject> 
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_prefs_connecting.png" format="PNG"/> 
              </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; applet preferences dialog; connecting section.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
              </mediaobject> 
              </screenshot> 
             </figure> 
             <para>Default: 
                   <itemizedlist>
                     <listitem><para><guilabel>Connect command</guilabel>: /sbin/ifup ppp0</para></listitem>
                     <listitem><para><guilabel>Disconnect command</guilabel>: /sbin/ifdown ppp0</para></listitem>
		     <listitem><para><guilabel>Confirm connection</guilabel>: yes</para></listitem>
                   </itemizedlist>
            </para>
 	    </listitem> 
  	  </varlistentry> 
	  <varlistentry>
            <term><guilabel>Display</guilabel></term>
            <listitem> 
              <para>You can select whether the &applet; applet will display the connect time and throughput status, 
                    how often it will update the status.</para>
              <figure id="fig-prefs-general-display"> 
                <title>Display Preferences</title> 
                <screenshot> 
                <mediaobject> 
                <imageobject>
                  <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_prefs_display.png" format="PNG"/> 
                </imageobject>
	        <textobject> 
                  <phrase>Shows &applet; applet preferences dialog; connecting section.</phrase> 
                </textobject> 
                </mediaobject> 
                </screenshot> 
              </figure> 
              <para>Default: 
                    <itemizedlist>
                      <listitem><para><guilabel>Updates per second</guilabel>: 5</para></listitem>
                      <listitem><para><guilabel>Show connect time and throughput</guilabel>: yes</para></listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
              </para>
            </listitem> 
 	  </varlistentry> 
        </variablelist> 
      </sect2>

      <sect2 id="modemlights-prefs-color">
        <title>Colors</title>
        <para>The <guilabel>Colors</guilabel> tab allows you to set colors for modem status for 
              Receive data, Send Data, Connection Status and the Text.
        </para>
      <figure id="fig-prefs-colors"> 
          <title>Colors Preferences</title>       
            <screenshot> 
            <mediaobject> 
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_colors.png" format="PNG"/> 
              </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; applet preferences dialog; connecting section.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
            </mediaobject> 
          </screenshot> 
        </figure> 
      </sect2>

      <sect2 id="modemlights-prefs-advanced">
        <title>Advanced</title>
        <para>The <guilabel>Advanced</guilabel> tab allows you to customize the 
              Modem options, and select whether to use the ISDN.
        </para>
        <figure id="fig-prefs-advanced"> 
          <title>Colors Preferences</title>       
            <screenshot> 
            <mediaobject> 
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="figures/modemlights_applet_advanced.png" format="PNG"/> 
              </imageobject>
	      <textobject> 
                <phrase>Shows &applet; applet preferences dialog; Advanced section.</phrase> 
              </textobject> 
            </mediaobject> 
          </screenshot> 
        </figure> 
        <para>You can enter a modem lock file in <guilabel>Modem lock file</guilabel>, device name in 
              <guilabel>Device</guilabel>, and specify whether to verify the owner of the lock file.
        </para>
        <para>You can click on the <guilabel>Use ISDN</guilabel> toggle button to select using ISDN instead
              of Modem.
        </para>
      </sect2>

  </sect1>

